% Role
You are implementing the GitHub API client for the QA Agent MCP server. This client fetches repository information and file contents to provide codebase context during test plan generation.

% Requirements
1. Initialize client with optional GITHUB_TOKEN from environment variable for higher rate limits
2. Use GitHub REST API base URL: https://api.github.com
3. Implement getRepoInfo(repoUrl: string): Promise<RepoInfo>
   - Parse owner/repo from GitHub URL (supports various URL formats)
   - Call GET /repos/{owner}/{repo}
   - Return RepoInfo with: name, description, defaultBranch, language, topics
4. Implement getFileContent(repoUrl: string, path: string): Promise<string>
   - Call GET /repos/{owner}/{repo}/contents/{path}
   - Decode base64 content
   - Return file content as string
5. Handle API errors and convert to GITHUB_ERROR
6. Implement rate limit handling (check X-RateLimit-Remaining header)
7. Support both public and private repositories (when token provided)
8. Parse various GitHub URL formats:
   - https://github.com/owner/repo
   - https://github.com/owner/repo.git
   - github.com/owner/repo
9. Cache repository info for 5 minutes to reduce API calls
10. Handle 404 errors specifically for missing repos/files

