% Instructions
- Use native fetch API for HTTP requests
- Define RepoInfo interface: { name: string, description: string, defaultBranch: string, language: string, topics: string[] }
- Add Authorization header when GITHUB_TOKEN is available
- Add Accept: application/vnd.github.v3+json header
- Add User-Agent header (required by GitHub API)
- Implement simple in-memory cache with TTL
- Decode file content from base64 (Buffer.from(content, 'base64').toString('utf-8'))
- Extract owner and repo from URL using regex
- Log rate limit status to stderr when approaching limits

% Deliverable
A TypeScript module at src/services/github-client.ts exporting functions for fetching GitHub repository information and file contents.

% Implementation Assumptions
- GITHUB_TOKEN environment variable is optional but recommended
- Network access to GitHub API is available
- Only text files are supported (not binary)
- Public repositories can be accessed without authentication
